Some wireless speakers, for example those used in home theater, use infrared technology to provide signal. These speakers are much less common, and with good reason: infrared signals cannot navigate walls or other obstacles. The music lover must therefore move the audio system to make sure that no such obstacles exist when using these speakers.

Wireless stereo speakers may be used in all sorts of weather, because they are extremely durable. It is not advisable to leave them outdoors during blizzards or any other unusually severe weather, but they can be left on a porch or lawn overnight without harmful effects. The durability does slightly affect the sound quality; protective materials can muffle sounds when the signal is coming from too far away.

When utilizing wireless speaker systems, just make sure you utilize common sense. Don't leave too large of the gap between your signal and also the speaker, and don't leave the speakers outside in poor weather. The speakers is going to be certain to deliver many years of quality music if their owners simply follow these guidelines.